## 3. State Management

### Approach
- **Primary:** `flutter_bloc` (BLoC + Cubit)
- **DI:** `get_it` for dependency injection
- **Storage:** `get_storage` + `flutter_secure_storage`

### Evaluation

| Aspect | Assessment |
|--------|------------|
| Consistency | ⚠️ Login/SignUp use **Bloc**, Profile uses **Cubit**. Mixed but acceptable |
| GetX dependency | 🔴 [get](file:///f:/Fodwa-App-main/lib/core/session/session_manager.dart#43-46) package is declared but never used — confusing for future devs |
| State preservation | ⚠️ LoginBloc manually carries over `isRemember`, `selectedTab`, `phoneNumber` across every state emission — very verbose and error-prone |
| BLoC coupling | 🔴 LoginBloc handles **login, forget password, verify OTP, reset password, AND profile image upload** — violates Single Responsibility |
| Scalability | ⚠️ Current approach is semi-scalable but the LoginBloc needs to be split. Profile feature has correct granularity |

---

## 4. Architecture Quality

### Strengths ✅
- Auth and Profile features follow **Clean Architecture** (data → domain → presentation)
- Use cases pattern is implemented
- Separation of data sources, repositories, and use cases exists
- `Result<T>` pattern for error handling
- Session management is centralized

### Critical Weaknesses 🔴

#### 4.1 Security — Exposed Secrets
```
# In end_points.dart
google_api_key = "AIzaSyBwKPVu6XJiG6FVdzcvAROW2nOAtGH1caY"

# In app_constants.dart
appSign = 'e4e456c1a7e52109c3f05361598149731f15d42fe55697425f68db7d70ae89b7'
oneSignalAppId = "cced843e-abcd-47ae-b444-e947ef337d1a"
oneSignalApiKey = "os_v2_app_ztwyipvlzvd25nce5fd66m35dknf6qiwsecudqmm63ogb3dfzqbtxbzksnyg6w3qota2nhqqrs6zlrptkyoxr2zhqgun5wkfddfvmwi"

# In dio_client.dart
baseUrl = "https://fodwa-backend-blbwk.ondigitalocean.app/api/users/"
```

> [!CAUTION]
> All API keys, signing secrets, and backend URLs are **hardcoded in source code**. These MUST be moved to environment variables / `--dart-define` / `.env` files excluded from version control.

#### 4.2 SSL Verification Disabled
In [dio_client.dart](file:///f:/Fodwa-App-main/lib/core/apiManager/dio_client.dart#L47-L52):
```dart
client.badCertificateCallback = (cert, host, port) => true;
```
This disables SSL certificate validation entirely — **critical security vulnerability** in production.

#### 4.3 Route Naming
In [app_router.dart](file:///f:/Fodwa-App-main/lib/config/routes/app_router.dart#L10-L29):
```dart
static const String bottomNav = "sdf/";
static const String login = "/sdfsdfsdfsdf";
static const String onBoard = "sf/";
static const String lectures = "sfsf/";
```
Route names are **nonsensical** — makes debugging and deep-linking impossible.

#### 4.4 `AppConfiguration.flavor` Never Initialized
[app_configeration.dart](file:///f:/Fodwa-App-main/lib/config/configeration/app_configeration.dart) declares `static late String flavor` but it is **never set** in [main()](file:///f:/Fodwa-App-main/lib/main.dart#10-35). Any access to `isDev` / `isProd` will crash at runtime.

#### 4.5 [AppKeys](file:///f:/Fodwa-App-main/lib/core/cahsing/app_keys.dart#1-14) Duplicate Key
```dart
static const String phone = "phone";
static const String section = "phone"; // ← same key as phone!
```

#### 4.6 Inconsistent Navigation
- [SplashScreen](file:///f:/Fodwa-App-main/lib/features/splash/splashScreen.dart#6-12) uses `Navigator.push()` (direct) instead of named routes
- [LoginScreen](file:///f:/Fodwa-App-main/lib/features/Auth/login/presentation/pages/login_screen.dart#22-31) uses `Navigator.pushAndRemoveUntil()` with MaterialPageRoute (direct)
- Some features reference named routes, others construct widgets directly
- **Mix of named routing and direct widget navigation** throughout

#### 4.7 [test_widgtet.dart](file:///f:/Fodwa-App-main/lib/core/sharedWidget/test_widgtet.dart) — 27KB Dead Code
[test_widgtet.dart](file:///f:/Fodwa-App-main/lib/core/sharedWidget/test_widgtet.dart) is a 27KB file that appears to be **entirely commented out**. This is dead weight.

#### 4.8 Firebase Declared But Not Initialized
`firebase_core`, `firebase_auth`, and `cloud_firestore` are in dependencies, but `Firebase.initializeApp()` is **never called** in [main()](file:///f:/Fodwa-App-main/lib/main.dart#10-35). Social login (Google/Apple) endpoints exist but Firebase is not wired up.

