## 5. Responsiveness Audit

### Sizing Approach
The app uses `AppConstants.h` and `AppConstants.w` — static late fields initialized from `MediaQuery` in `SplashScreen.build()` and `BottomNav.build()`.

```dart
static late double h;
static late double w;
static void initSize(BuildContext context) {
  h = MediaQuery.of(context).size.height;
  w = MediaQuery.of(context).size.width;
}
```

### Issues

| Risk | Description |
|------|-------------|
| 🔴 **Static late fields** | `h` and `w` are set once and never update. Screen rotation, split-screen, or foldable devices will have stale values |
| 🔴 **No LayoutBuilder** | Zero usage of `LayoutBuilder` detected across the entire codebase |
| 🔴 **No responsive breakpoints** | No tablet vs phone distinction anywhere |
| ⚠️ **Fixed pixel widths** | [large_field.dart](file:///f:/Fodwa-App-main/lib/core/sharedWidget/large_field.dart) line 115: `width: 327` (hardcoded pixel value) |
| ⚠️ **[custom_loading.dart](file:///f:/Fodwa-App-main/lib/core/sharedWidget/custom_loading.dart)** | `width: 60`, `width: 40` — fixed pixel sizes |
| ⚠️ **BottomAppBar height** | `height: AppConstants.h * 0.102` — may be too tall or short on extreme screen sizes |

### Screens at Risk
| Screen | Risk Level | Reason |
|--------|------------|--------|
| All screens | ⚠️ Medium | Rely on `AppConstants.h/w` which never refreshes |
| [large_field.dart](file:///f:/Fodwa-App-main/lib/core/sharedWidget/large_field.dart) | 🔴 High | Hardcoded `width: 327` pixels |
| [custom_loading.dart](file:///f:/Fodwa-App-main/lib/core/sharedWidget/custom_loading.dart) | ⚠️ Medium | Fixed 40/60px sizes |
| [success_widget.dart](file:///f:/Fodwa-App-main/lib/core/sharedWidget/success_widget.dart) | ⚠️ Medium | Uses `AppConstants.w * 0.872` — okay for phones, may not work on tablets |
| Profile screens | ⚠️ Medium | Many `AppConstants.h * 0.0067` spacing values — too tiny on small screens |

### Recommendation
Replace `AppConstants.h/w` with `MediaQuery.of(context)` or `LayoutBuilder` at the widget level. Consider adopting the `flutter_screenutil` package or a responsive helper that recomputes on layout changes.

